Sentencas: Strontium- and copper-doped lanthanum ferrite (LaSrCuFe) was used as new cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with scandia-stabilized zirconia electrolyte at intermediate temperatures.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of a ScMnSZ/LaSrCuFe cell with GDC interlayer for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The performance of an anode-supported single cell prepared using a Ni/YSZ anode, ScMnSZ ((ZrO2)(0.89)(Sc2O3)(0.1)(MnO2)(0.01)) electrolyte, and a LaSrCuFe cathode was evaluated.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of a ScMnSZ/LaSrCuFe cell with GDC interlayer for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects on the cell performance of the GDC (GD(0.1)Ce(0.9)O(1.95)) interlayer between the electrolyte and cathode were also investigated.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of a ScMnSZ/LaSrCuFe cell with GDC interlayer for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The microstructure and chemical composition of the cell were analyzed using a scanning electron microscope (SEM) equipped with an energy dispersive X-ray analyzer (EDS).
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of a ScMnSZ/LaSrCuFe cell with GDC interlayer for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: AC impedance spectroscopy was used to measure the polarization resistance of a single cell.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of a ScMnSZ/LaSrCuFe cell with GDC interlayer for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results highlight the promising combination of ScMnSZ electrolyte and LaSrCuFe cathode material in terms of chemical compatibility and electrical performance.
Titulo: Fabrication and performance of a ScMnSZ/LaSrCuFe cell with GDC interlayer for solid oxide fuel cells
